derivation.yuyuan_name: late 19th cent.: from Dum Dum, name of a town and arsenal near Calcutta, India, where such bullets were first produced

entry.tran: 达姆弹(一种弹头很软或中空的子弹,击中后爆炸成碎片,会造成严重伤害)
entry.def: A dum-dum or a dum-dum bullet is a bullet that is very soft or hollow at the front. Dum-dum bullets cause large and serious wounds because they break into small pieces and spread out when they hit someone.

means.word_mean: 1. a soft-nosed small-arms bullet that expands when it hits a target and causes a gaping wound
